   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Birmingham_1822_04_23_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  8 - Holles Street<lb/>
                  <date when="1822-04-23">April 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. 1822</date><lb/></dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BowrJ1">
                            Dear Sir<lb/>
                        </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am happy to be <choice>
                  <orig>disen<lb/>
                        -gaged</orig>
                  <reg>disengaged</reg>
               </choice> on one of the days<lb/>
                    you propose. On Wednesday the<lb/>
                    first; when we shall do<lb/>
                    ourselves the pleasure of<lb/>
                    waiting upon you<lb/>
                    I will take the liberty<lb/>
                    of bringing with me a<lb/>
                    friend of mine who has<lb/>
                    an ardent desire to be made<lb/>
                    acquainted with those who<lb/>
                    have served <del>so</del> eminently<lb/>
                    the African cause - my<lb/>
               friend is <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1"><choice><abbr>Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></abbr><reg>Captain</reg></choice> Beaufort</persName>
               <lb/>
                    (author of a book you may<lb/>
                    have met with, <hi rend="underline">
                  <title ref="./Workography.xml#Karam1">
                     <choice>
                        <orig>Karaman<lb/>
                    nia</orig>
                        <reg>Karamannia</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </title>
               </hi> - remarkable for <choice>
                  <orig>contain<lb/>
                        ing</orig>
                  <reg>containing</reg>
               </choice> in a small octavo what<lb/>
                    most modern travellers<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Birmingham_1822_04_23_page02.jpg"/>
            <p>would have swelled to one<lb/>
                    quarto at the least -<lb/>
                    If your table should<lb/>
                    be full you will be so<lb/>
                    good to write a line to<lb/>
                    tell me so frankly and I<lb/>
                    will not put my friend<lb/>
                    in the disagreeable <choice>
                  <orig>predic<lb/>
                        -ment</orig>
                  <reg>predicament</reg>
               </choice> of being one too many<lb/>
               With my sisters <choice><abbr>comp<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi></abbr><reg>compliments</reg></choice>
               <lb/>
               and my own to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BowrX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Bowring</persName><lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    I am Dear Sir<lb/>
                    Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>You do not name your<lb/>
                        dinner hour.</p><lb/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               
                  <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Birmingham_1822_04_23_page03.jpg"/>
                  <note><persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
                  <lb/>
                     23 April 1822<lb/></note>
